OL,3,CBoy who was told he would never walk
OL,4,Ctakes first steps thanks to sensory
OL,5,Ccentre
OL,7,F"To have Chailey as a partner going,
OL,8,Fyes, we can see that potential in your
OL,9,Fchild, 'we're going to try this, we're
OL,10,Fgoing to try that, no, that didn't
OL,11,Fwork, let's find a different option',
OL,12,Fand they've kind of constantly been
OL,13,Fsearching for what works specifically
OL,14,Ffor him.
OL,16,F"That has been amazing for us.
OL,18,F"But it's finding what he needs to
OL,19,Fhelp him achieve what he's capable of."
